-- Today, we'll practice about COALESCE, It is used to return the first non-null value in a list of expressions.
-- In this example, we will use the COALESCE function to handle null values in our dataset.

SELECT Product_Name, 
     COALESCE(Product_Category, 'UNKNOWN_CATEGORY') AS Product_Category
FROM
 superstore.superstore_sales_data;

 /*Now, this query will return the Product_Name and Product_Category, replacing any null values in the Product_Category column
  with 'UNKNOWN_CATEGORY'. This is useful for ensuring that our dataset does not have any missing values in the Product_Category
   field, which can be important for analysis and reporting. */
/* NOTE: This does not permanently fills the NULL's, It is only for current query results, To permanently fix the NULL's, 
UPDATE clause has to be used instead. */

